data.description: Redeemed to Perfection! No detail has been spared with this one-of-a-kind custom rehab that perfectly marries the historic beauty of the original wood floors and exposed brick walls with luxury custom finishings and modern amenities that check off all the boxes in your want column. Custom 2016 renovation features new systems including zoned HVAC, a main level with large open living/eating floor plan, custom cabinets, granite counter tops, and stainless appliances. Outside you'll find a 2-story deck and a 2 car garage-port. The 2nd floor boasts a master suite with his/hers closets, full hall bath, 2 more bedrooms, and laundry room. The basement has an additional bedroom, full bath, office and rec room space. Aside from all the amazingness the home offers, this neighborhood has great amenities too. A short walk from Whisk, Mud House, other Cherokee Street businesses, and Benton Park. Hands down the absolute best part is the neighbors you will soon be calling friends.
